<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3331] DropDownChoice with wantOnSelectionChangedNotifications fails without Form</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3331</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you have a DDC without a form, then in onSelectionChanged the new selection will be always null. As soon as you put a Form around the DDC, it just starts to work.&lt;br/&gt;
Although the HTML 4 DTD does not allow a select tag outside a form, Wicket supported this behaviour, and this feature also worked with 1.5-M3 too.&lt;br/&gt;
See the attached project showing that the newSelection is null if the DDC is not inside a form.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
